</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,225,251]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[324,539,224,250]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="smitti">
<emphasis box="[324,539,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Ophiacantha smitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from both sides of the Atlantic, is one of the more recent additions to the deep-water echinoderm fauna from the 
<collectingRegion box="[722,804,261,287]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Azores</collectingRegion>
, identify by 
<bibRefCitation author="Segonzac, M." box="[944,1229,260,287]" firstAuthor="St ˆ hr" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="383 - 402" refId="ref201413" refString="St ˆ hr, S. &amp; Segonzac, M. (2005) Deep-sea ophiuroids (Echinodermata) from reducing and non-reducing environments in the North Atlantic Ocean. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 85 (2), 383 - 402. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315405011318 h" type="journal article" year="2005">St̂hr &amp; Segonzac (2005)</bibRefCitation>
in a non-vent area near Lucky Strike (
<emphasis box="[368,487,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L’Atalante</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[501,624,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Victor 1ère</emphasis>
cruise, sta 
<collectionCode box="[750,787,297,323]" country="Czech Republic" name="Západoceské muzeum v Plzni" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="Museum">PL</collectionCode>
33: 
<geoCoordinate box="[826,966,296,323]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="15" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="15" seconds="45" value="37.2625">37°15’45”N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[977,1120,297,323]" degrees="32" direction="west" minutes="13" orientation="longitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" precision="15" seconds="30" value="-32.225002">32°13’30”W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[1132,1228,296,323]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="m" value="1.55">1,550 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
